article.description: Seneca Knight scored 22 points and grabbed eight rebounds as San Jose State beat Grambling State 83-76 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Knight with 22 leads San Jose St. past Grambling 83-76
article.linkText: Knight with 22 leads San Jose St. past Grambling 83-76
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Seneca Knight scored 22 points and grabbed eight rebounds as San Jose State beat Grambling State 83-76 on Wednesday night. Craig LeCesne added 17 points and six rebounds for the Spartans (3-2). Christian Anigwe had 14 points and 10 rebounds and Zach Chappell had 10 points off the bench. The Spartans outrebounded Grambling 41-32. Ivy Smith Jr. led the Tigers (3-1) with 19 points. Devante Jackson added 15 points. ---- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
